#Sun King Sales Data
sql1 = """
    SELECT 
           accounts.angaza_id,
           accounts.area_derived as area,
           accounts.region,
           accounts.country,
           COALESCE(
               NULLIF(accounts.unit_location_latitudelongitude,''),
               NULLIF(accounts.registration_location_latitudelongitude,'')
               ) AS latlong, -- get coordinates from whatever column has it
           split_part(latlong,',', 1)::DECIMAL(6,4)  AS "unit_lat",
           split_part(latlong,',', 2)::DECIMAL(7,4)  AS "unit_long"           

      FROM easybuy.accounts_final_pdt AS accounts
     WHERE split_part(latlong,',',2) <> '' -- check for valid gps  
       AND accounts.registration_date_utc::DATETIME       >    GETDATE() - INTERVAL '1 year' -- within 1 year
       AND accounts.country                               =    'Kenya'
           -- AND product_group LIKE 'SHS%'
       --AND region = 'Nyanza' -- Kenya
           -- AND area in ('Akoko') -- Nigeria
     LIMIT 1e7
     """

x = np.arange(xmin, xmax, res)
y = np.arange(ymin, ymax, res)
array = np.zeros((len(y), len(x)))
xi = None
# Count the points in each cell
for idx, row in gdf2.iterrows():
    xi = np.searchsorted(x, row.geometry.x, side = 'right') - 1
    yi = np.searchsorted(y, row.geometry.y, side = 'right') - 1
    array[yi, xi] += 1
# Create a raster to visualize in matplotlib
transform1 = from_origin(xmin, ymax, res, res)
